6. TERMINATION

6.1. Automatic Termination for Breach

This License and the rights granted hereunder will terminate automatically upon 
any material breach by You of the terms or conditions of this License. Such 
termination shall be automatic and shall not require notice from the Licensor.

Material breaches include, but are not limited to:
    (a) Failure to comply with the attribution requirements of Section 3.2;
    (b) Failure to comply with the reciprocal licensing mandate of Section 3.3;
    (c) Failure to provide Source Code as required by Section 3.4;
    (d) Distribution of the Program or Derivative Works under terms other than 
        this License;
    (e) Removal or alteration of copyright notices or license terms;
    (f) Misrepresentation of the origin of the Program or Derivative Works.

6.2. Effect of Termination

Upon termination of this License for any reason:
    (a) You must immediately cease all use, reproduction, distribution, and 
        modification of the Program and all Derivative Works;
    (b) You must destroy or permanently delete all copies of the Program and 
        Derivative Works in Your possession or control, including all backup 
        copies;
    (c) You must certify in writing to the Licensor that all copies have been 
        destroyed or deleted, if requested by the Licensor;
    (d) Any sublicenses previously granted by You that are compliant with this 
        License shall survive such termination, provided that such sublicensees 
        remain in full compliance with this License.

6.3. Survival

Sections 4 (Disclaimer of Warranty), 5 (Limitation of Liability), 6.2 (Effect 
of Termination), 6.3 (Survival), and 7 (General Provisions) shall survive any 
termination of this License.

6.4. Reinstatement

If You cure the breach within thirty (30) days of becoming aware of the breach, 
then Your rights under this License are automatically reinstated. However, this 
reinstatement provision does not apply to repeat violations or intentional 
breaches.

